  "body": "Hi there,\r\n\r\nplease note that this is an issue tracker reserved for bug reports and feature requests.\r\n\r\nFor general questions please use the gitter channel or the Ethereum stack exchange at https://ethereum.stackexchange.com.\r\n\r\nI  use geth 1.8.21 and synced the block data in light mode.  Then I  search block and transaction in geth console.  However, I got the right block, but  when I  search the transaction by `eth.getTransaction(\"txHash\")` which is from `transactions` list. I got  `null`.  Anyone who met this case? why it happened? \r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.8.21-stable`\r\nOS & Version: Windows/Linux/OSX\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\n` eth.getTransaction(\"0x736d4a2e625544ceff964ad1808823c9c7436478c625ef9da73650d6f9744258\")`  get the right tx infomation.  \r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\n```\r\n> eth.getTransaction(\"0x736d4a2e625544ceff964ad1808823c9c7436478c625ef9da73650d6f9744258\")\r\nnull\r\n```\r\n\r\nBTW,  I am sure the block I use is confirmed.  and  `getBalance`, `getBlock` api work fine.\r\n",
